WEBVTT

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:05.760 align:middle line:90%
[MUSIC PLAYING]

00:00:05.760 --> 00:00:07.690 align:middle line:90%


00:00:07.690 --> 00:00:10.090 align:middle line:84%
>> Land art, sometimes
known as earthworks,

00:00:10.090 --> 00:00:14.164 align:middle line:84%
is an art movement that
started in the USA.

00:00:14.164 --> 00:00:18.240 align:middle line:84%
>> Land art is a combination
with something created

00:00:18.240 --> 00:00:24.810 align:middle line:84%
by an artist and what
already is in place.

00:00:24.810 --> 00:00:25.610 align:middle line:90%
[SPEAKING FRENCH]

00:00:25.610 --> 00:00:29.090 align:middle line:84%
>> Instead of paper of
canvas, I needed space.

00:00:29.090 --> 00:00:35.630 align:middle line:84%
>> Nature offers so many
opportunities for seeing in new

00:00:35.630 --> 00:00:36.540 align:middle line:90%
ways.

00:00:36.540 --> 00:00:38.882 align:middle line:84%
>> Land art was when we
discovered really what it

00:00:38.882 --> 00:00:39.840 align:middle line:90%
looked like from above.

00:00:39.840 --> 00:00:45.600 align:middle line:90%
[MUSIC PLAYING]

00:00:45.600 --> 00:00:50.900 align:middle line:90%


00:00:50.900 --> 00:00:55.070 align:middle line:84%
>> Viewed from the sky, land
art reveals its vastness and art

00:00:55.070 --> 00:00:56.660 align:middle line:90%
in landscape dimensions.

00:00:56.660 --> 00:00:59.190 align:middle line:90%


00:00:59.190 --> 00:01:02.610 align:middle line:84%
This form of contemporary art
uses the natural elements--

00:01:02.610 --> 00:01:06.950 align:middle line:84%
wood, stone, water,
earth, plants, sand.

00:01:06.950 --> 00:01:08.200 align:middle line:90%
>> [SPEAKING FOREIGN LANGUAGE]

00:01:08.200 --> 00:01:11.500 align:middle line:84%
You could call it a
honeymoon with nature.

00:01:11.500 --> 00:01:14.220 align:middle line:90%
>> It's a dance with nature.

00:01:14.220 --> 00:01:18.700 align:middle line:84%
>> The people who see it
are affected in some way.

00:01:18.700 --> 00:01:22.060 align:middle line:84%
>> These artists have left their
workshops for a new dimension,

00:01:22.060 --> 00:01:23.170 align:middle line:90%
a voyage of initiation.

00:01:23.170 --> 00:01:24.420 align:middle line:90%
>> [SPEAKING FOREIGN LANGUAGE]

00:01:24.420 --> 00:01:26.890 align:middle line:84%
>> It's temporary, and that's
what makes it interesting.

00:01:26.890 --> 00:01:29.710 align:middle line:84%
>> Anything we can create will
eventually fade away and will

00:01:29.710 --> 00:01:32.160 align:middle line:90%
be forgotten.

00:01:32.160 --> 00:01:35.600 align:middle line:84%
>> Beneath the open sky, their
art galleries and museums are

00:01:35.600 --> 00:01:36.580 align:middle line:90%
called planet Earth.

00:01:36.580 --> 00:01:41.530 align:middle line:90%


00:01:41.530 --> 00:01:43.720 align:middle line:84%
To discover the
beauty of land art,

00:01:43.720 --> 00:01:46.120 align:middle line:84%
we will travel the world
to visit some of the most

00:01:46.120 --> 00:01:49.630 align:middle line:84%
spectacular artworks
as seen from above,

00:01:49.630 --> 00:01:52.600 align:middle line:84%
a journey that begins with
the more permanent pieces,

00:01:52.600 --> 00:01:54.080 align:middle line:90%
ending with temporary works.

00:01:54.080 --> 00:02:02.930 align:middle line:90%


00:02:02.930 --> 00:02:05.860 align:middle line:10%
This artistic movement
believes that art and nature

00:02:05.860 --> 00:02:07.970 align:middle line:10%
are inseparable.

00:02:07.970 --> 00:02:10.240 align:middle line:84%
The first works were
created in the grand desert

00:02:10.240 --> 00:02:16.670 align:middle line:84%
landscapes of western
America in the late 1960s.

00:02:16.670 --> 00:02:19.070 align:middle line:10%
Like many movements
at the time, land art

00:02:19.070 --> 00:02:21.260 align:middle line:10%
was a way of connecting
art and life,

00:02:21.260 --> 00:02:23.570 align:middle line:10%
fleeing traditional
museum exhibitions

00:02:23.570 --> 00:02:26.480 align:middle line:10%
and the financial
circuits of galleries.

00:02:26.480 --> 00:02:28.760 align:middle line:84%
Some installations are
monumental and require

00:02:28.760 --> 00:02:30.870 align:middle line:90%
a tremendous amount of work.

00:02:30.870 --> 00:02:33.490 align:middle line:84%
Today, many have become
accessible and permanent

00:02:33.490 --> 00:02:34.922 align:middle line:90%
through photography.

00:02:34.922 --> 00:02:37.880 align:middle line:90%


00:02:37.880 --> 00:02:41.000 align:middle line:84%
In the USA, the town
of Alliance in Nebraska

00:02:41.000 --> 00:02:45.020 align:middle line:84%
is the home of an artwork that
is pulling in the tourists.

00:02:45.020 --> 00:02:48.470 align:middle line:84%
Fascinated by the prehistoric
monument of Stonehenge,

00:02:48.470 --> 00:02:58.160 align:middle line:84%
Jim Reinders created a replica
in 1986 with vintage cars.

00:02:58.160 --> 00:03:01.160 align:middle line:84%
>> Carhenge is sort of the
21st century reproduction

00:03:01.160 --> 00:03:02.120 align:middle line:90%
of Stonehenge.

00:03:02.120 --> 00:03:10.090 align:middle line:90%


00:03:10.090 --> 00:03:12.580 align:middle line:84%
>> No stone or rocks
were in the vicinity,

00:03:12.580 --> 00:03:17.020 align:middle line:84%
so Jim took what was at hand,
cars from the 1940s and '50s.

00:03:17.020 --> 00:03:18.565 align:middle line:90%
Jeep, Plymouth, Cadillac.

00:03:18.565 --> 00:03:21.568 align:middle line:90%


00:03:21.568 --> 00:03:24.200 align:middle line:84%
At the time, the
piece intrigued.

00:03:24.200 --> 00:03:26.440 align:middle line:84%
Some locals even
called it a junkyard.

00:03:26.440 --> 00:03:29.870 align:middle line:90%


00:03:29.870 --> 00:03:32.370 align:middle line:84%
>> They were getting in trouble
for having junk cars sitting

00:03:32.370 --> 00:03:33.170 align:middle line:90%
out there.

00:03:33.170 --> 00:03:35.040 align:middle line:84%
>> The town back then
seemed a bit divided.

00:03:35.040 --> 00:03:35.580 align:middle line:90%
>> They were divided on it.

00:03:35.580 --> 00:03:36.380 align:middle line:90%
On it.

00:03:36.380 --> 00:03:38.147 align:middle line:84%
with more of a creative
mind would say,

00:03:38.147 --> 00:03:39.230 align:middle line:90%
oh, it's going to be neat.

00:03:39.230 --> 00:03:39.780 align:middle line:90%
It's a piece of art.

00:03:39.780 --> 00:03:41.250 align:middle line:84%
And then there were some
that just said, it's--

00:03:41.250 --> 00:03:42.050 align:middle line:90%
>> It's junk.

00:03:42.050 --> 00:03:44.880 align:middle line:84%
>> There were a lot of citizens
that really didn't like

00:03:44.880 --> 00:03:46.740 align:middle line:90%
Carhenge for a lot of years.

00:03:46.740 --> 00:03:49.410 align:middle line:84%
They thought it was
unsightly, and they

00:03:49.410 --> 00:03:53.160 align:middle line:84%
didn't want a junkyard
representing their town.

00:03:53.160 --> 00:03:56.550 align:middle line:84%
>> Carhenge was abandoned
and left to rust.

00:03:56.550 --> 00:03:58.920 align:middle line:10%
>> People came out, and
they just drank out here,

00:03:58.920 --> 00:04:01.350 align:middle line:10%
left empty beer cans,
and everything like that.

00:04:01.350 --> 00:04:03.540 align:middle line:10%
Just littered all
over the place.

00:04:03.540 --> 00:04:07.030 align:middle line:10%
It wasn't someplace
you wanted to go.

00:04:07.030 --> 00:04:09.940 align:middle line:84%
>> Local authorities have
recently taken control,

00:04:09.940 --> 00:04:13.180 align:middle line:84%
and the site has since
become an attraction.

00:04:13.180 --> 00:04:14.550 align:middle line:90%
>> Artists started noticing it.

00:04:14.550 --> 00:04:15.383 align:middle line:90%
>> Artists started--

00:04:15.383 --> 00:04:17.360 align:middle line:84%
>> And instead of it
being junk, it became art.

00:04:17.360 --> 00:04:18.160 align:middle line:90%
>> Yes.

00:04:18.160 --> 00:04:22.180 align:middle line:84%
>> People started to get an
understanding of how many

00:04:22.180 --> 00:04:25.540 align:middle line:84%
people come to see
this particular view

00:04:25.540 --> 00:04:27.790 align:middle line:90%
of someone's art.

00:04:27.790 --> 00:04:31.750 align:middle line:84%
>> Today, Carhenge attracts
80,000 tourists a year,

00:04:31.750 --> 00:04:34.450 align:middle line:84%
and the local inhabitants of
Nebraska have since learned

00:04:34.450 --> 00:04:37.540 align:middle line:84%
to appreciate and respect
this rather unusual creation.

00:04:37.540 --> 00:04:44.960 align:middle line:90%


00:04:44.960 --> 00:04:48.060 align:middle line:84%
Far from the crowds in the
Sahara Desert of Morocco

00:04:48.060 --> 00:04:50.580 align:middle line:84%
is where the German
artist Hannsjorg Voth

00:04:50.580 --> 00:04:57.230 align:middle line:90%
decided to settle back in 1987.

00:04:57.230 --> 00:05:00.590 align:middle line:84%
Like a hermit, he created
three monumental artworks

00:05:00.590 --> 00:05:03.890 align:middle line:84%
over a period of 20 years
on this vast sandy canvas.

00:05:03.890 --> 00:05:06.710 align:middle line:90%


00:05:06.710 --> 00:05:09.350 align:middle line:84%
His adventure began with
this astounding "Stairway

00:05:09.350 --> 00:05:13.740 align:middle line:90%
to Heaven," 16 meters high.

00:05:13.740 --> 00:05:15.480 align:middle line:90%
>> [SPEAKING GERMAN]

00:05:15.480 --> 00:05:19.800 align:middle line:84%
>> I named it
"Stairway to Heaven"

00:05:19.800 --> 00:05:27.000 align:middle line:84%
in reference to transcendence, a
Latin word that implies a shift

00:05:27.000 --> 00:05:30.510 align:middle line:90%
in human boundaries.

00:05:30.510 --> 00:05:35.490 align:middle line:84%
That is what transcendence
is really all about,

00:05:35.490 --> 00:05:38.120 align:middle line:90%
because we are all ephemeral.

00:05:38.120 --> 00:05:41.710 align:middle line:90%
There's an end to everything.

00:05:41.710 --> 00:05:45.070 align:middle line:84%
>> A staircase that stands
proudly towards the sky like

00:05:45.070 --> 00:05:46.140 align:middle line:90%
humans.

00:05:46.140 --> 00:05:49.380 align:middle line:84%
Only here, it is crafted
out of compressed clay.

00:05:49.380 --> 00:05:50.550 align:middle line:90%
>> [SPEAKING GERMAN]

00:05:50.550 --> 00:05:55.110 align:middle line:84%
>> When I was drawing
the "Stairway to Heaven,"

00:05:55.110 --> 00:05:59.430 align:middle line:84%
I had the intention to build
it in a remote and secret

00:05:59.430 --> 00:06:03.140 align:middle line:84%
location, somewhere
hard to get to.

00:06:03.140 --> 00:06:06.450 align:middle line:84%
And that is one of the
reasons I went to Morocco.

00:06:06.450 --> 00:06:09.390 align:middle line:90%


00:06:09.390 --> 00:06:13.290 align:middle line:84%
I wanted to build it from
earth that would in time return

00:06:13.290 --> 00:06:14.610 align:middle line:90%
To the earth.

00:06:14.610 --> 00:06:18.120 align:middle line:84%
That meant living in the
project, working on it,

00:06:18.120 --> 00:06:20.640 align:middle line:90%
and then letting it go.

00:06:20.640 --> 00:06:22.650 align:middle line:84%
Letting the piece
return to dust.

00:06:22.650 --> 00:06:27.190 align:middle line:90%


00:06:27.190 --> 00:06:30.107 align:middle line:84%
>> Mohamed is the
caretaker of this land art.

00:06:30.107 --> 00:06:32.910 align:middle line:90%


00:06:32.910 --> 00:06:35.690 align:middle line:84%
For him, the stairway
has a different purpose,

00:06:35.690 --> 00:06:38.954 align:middle line:84%
a more matter of fact one
than this vast desert.

00:06:38.954 --> 00:06:40.300 align:middle line:90%
>> [SPEAKING FOREIGN LANGUAGE]

00:06:40.300 --> 00:06:43.890 align:middle line:84%
>> For us nomads, we climb
the staircase to look out

00:06:43.890 --> 00:06:47.490 align:middle line:84%
at the horizon and check if rain
is coming or if other nomads

00:06:47.490 --> 00:06:49.230 align:middle line:90%
are settling in the area.

00:06:49.230 --> 00:06:51.600 align:middle line:84%
If We can see if
a storm is brewing

00:06:51.600 --> 00:06:55.140 align:middle line:84%
or if there are greener
areas for our animals.

00:06:55.140 --> 00:06:58.300 align:middle line:84%
It also gives us shade when
the heat is suffocating.

00:06:58.300 --> 00:07:01.920 align:middle line:90%


00:07:01.920 --> 00:07:03.260 align:middle line:90%
>> [SPEAKING GERMAN]

00:07:03.260 --> 00:07:07.970 align:middle line:84%
>> When there is a sandstorm,
all the animals disperse.

00:07:07.970 --> 00:07:11.000 align:middle line:84%
When the nomads climb to
the top of the stairway,

00:07:11.000 --> 00:07:13.610 align:middle line:84%
they can locate them
easier with the help

00:07:13.610 --> 00:07:15.740 align:middle line:90%
of a pair of binoculars.

00:07:15.740 --> 00:07:17.180 align:middle line:90%
That's OK for me.

00:07:17.180 --> 00:07:20.000 align:middle line:84%
It wasn't my initial
intention, but I don't

00:07:20.000 --> 00:07:21.500 align:middle line:90%
expect them to think as we do.

00:07:21.500 --> 00:07:28.940 align:middle line:90%


00:07:28.940 --> 00:07:32.090 align:middle line:84%
>> Each step takes us back
through our own history

00:07:32.090 --> 00:07:34.985 align:middle line:84%
to a time when humanity was
in harmony with the gods.

00:07:34.985 --> 00:07:41.210 align:middle line:90%


00:07:41.210 --> 00:07:42.650 align:middle line:90%
>> [SPEAKING FOREIGN LANGUAGE]

00:07:42.650 --> 00:07:47.110 align:middle line:84%
For us, God is in
the seventh heaven,

00:07:47.110 --> 00:07:48.850 align:middle line:84%
and you can't get
there by climbing

00:07:48.850 --> 00:07:51.030 align:middle line:90%
50-odd steps on a stairway.

00:07:51.030 --> 00:07:59.880 align:middle line:90%


00:07:59.880 --> 00:08:02.790 align:middle line:84%
>> A few minutes' ride from
the "Stairway to Heaven"

00:08:02.790 --> 00:08:05.620 align:middle line:84%
is the second earthwork
of Hannsjorg Voth,

00:08:05.620 --> 00:08:06.490 align:middle line:90%
the "Golden Spiral."

00:08:06.490 --> 00:08:10.040 align:middle line:90%


00:08:10.040 --> 00:08:13.990 align:middle line:84%
Named by Mohamed as The
Snail, it holds in its center

00:08:13.990 --> 00:08:17.330 align:middle line:90%
a well over 17 meters deep.

00:08:17.330 --> 00:08:19.310 align:middle line:84%
Water, the most
essential element

00:08:19.310 --> 00:08:21.831 align:middle line:84%
for survival in this
hostile environment.

00:08:21.831 --> 00:08:25.520 align:middle line:90%


00:08:25.520 --> 00:08:27.260 align:middle line:84%
All the harmony
of this edifice is

00:08:27.260 --> 00:08:31.260 align:middle line:84%
based on prodigious
proportions, the golden section.

00:08:31.260 --> 00:08:34.070 align:middle line:90%
>> [SPEAKING GERMAN]

00:08:34.070 --> 00:08:38.900 align:middle line:84%
The "Golden Section" has been
used by artists and architects

00:08:38.900 --> 00:08:43.130 align:middle line:84%
since the ancient
Greeks in order

00:08:43.130 --> 00:08:47.270 align:middle line:84%
to create a perfect
aesthetic design,

00:08:47.270 --> 00:08:49.325 align:middle line:84%
and I used it in
the "Golden Spiral."

00:08:49.325 --> 00:08:56.490 align:middle line:90%


00:08:56.490 --> 00:09:00.120 align:middle line:84%
>> On the horizon, the third
piece of the artist stands out

00:09:00.120 --> 00:09:01.225 align:middle line:90%
clearly like a castle.

00:09:01.225 --> 00:09:09.980 align:middle line:90%


00:09:09.980 --> 00:09:13.670 align:middle line:84%
The "City of Orion" refers
to the distinct constellation

00:09:13.670 --> 00:09:16.180 align:middle line:90%
of stars named Orion.

00:09:16.180 --> 00:09:17.120 align:middle line:90%
>> [SPEAKING GERMAN]

00:09:17.120 --> 00:09:21.840 align:middle line:84%
>> I think the "City of
Orion" is highly mythological.

00:09:21.840 --> 00:09:24.340 align:middle line:84%
Orion comes from
Greek mythology.

00:09:24.340 --> 00:09:28.620 align:middle line:90%


00:09:28.620 --> 00:09:31.620 align:middle line:84%
>> According to the legend,
Orion represents a hunter that

00:09:31.620 --> 00:09:33.480 align:middle line:84%
has the power to
kill any animal.

00:09:33.480 --> 00:09:36.380 align:middle line:90%


00:09:36.380 --> 00:09:38.630 align:middle line:90%
Mohamed knows the legend well.

00:09:38.630 --> 00:09:41.470 align:middle line:84%
He can draw the "City
of Orion" in the sand,

00:09:41.470 --> 00:09:45.080 align:middle line:84%
linking all 24 stars that
make up a man holding a bow.

00:09:45.080 --> 00:09:48.110 align:middle line:90%


00:09:48.110 --> 00:09:50.150 align:middle line:84%
For the artist, each
piece of land art

00:09:50.150 --> 00:09:53.040 align:middle line:84%
has a message and
representation.

00:09:53.040 --> 00:09:56.090 align:middle line:84%
The "Stairway to Heaven"
is transcendence.

00:09:56.090 --> 00:09:58.310 align:middle line:90%
The "Golden Spiral" is revival.

00:09:58.310 --> 00:10:02.070 align:middle line:84%
And the "City of Orion"
is that of the cosmos.

00:10:02.070 --> 00:10:03.550 align:middle line:90%
>> [SPEAKING GERMAN]

00:10:03.550 --> 00:10:07.470 align:middle line:84%
>> It's three sculptures that I
did like that without thinking

00:10:07.470 --> 00:10:10.260 align:middle line:84%
about it, but they
work well together.

00:10:10.260 --> 00:10:16.280 align:middle line:90%


00:10:16.280 --> 00:10:18.720 align:middle line:84%
What is most important
is that I was

00:10:18.720 --> 00:10:21.930 align:middle line:84%
able to work in peace
for roughly 15 years

00:10:21.930 --> 00:10:27.110 align:middle line:84%
without being disturbed,
to go deep inside of me

00:10:27.110 --> 00:10:28.810 align:middle line:90%
and follow my intention.

00:10:28.810 --> 00:10:33.950 align:middle line:90%


00:10:33.950 --> 00:10:36.040 align:middle line:84%
>> To help finance
his art in the desert,

00:10:36.040 --> 00:10:38.630 align:middle line:84%
Hannsjorg Voth held
several exhibitions.

00:10:38.630 --> 00:10:40.520 align:middle line:84%
But the cost of
this public exposure

00:10:40.520 --> 00:10:42.873 align:middle line:90%
had considerable consequences.

00:10:42.873 --> 00:10:44.870 align:middle line:90%
>> [SPEAKING FOREIGN LANGUAGE]

00:10:44.870 --> 00:10:48.550 align:middle line:84%
>> From that moment
on came the investors,

00:10:48.550 --> 00:10:52.580 align:middle line:84%
the Europeans and the Spanish
with their four-wheel drives

00:10:52.580 --> 00:10:54.910 align:middle line:90%
that destroyed the landscape.

00:10:54.910 --> 00:10:58.480 align:middle line:90%
And when disturbed, I leave.

00:10:58.480 --> 00:11:02.340 align:middle line:84%
>> The arrival of visitors and
tourists put an end to 20 years

00:11:02.340 --> 00:11:03.430 align:middle line:90%
of creation.

00:11:03.430 --> 00:11:04.970 align:middle line:90%
>> [SPEAKING GERMAN]

00:11:04.970 --> 00:11:06.600 align:middle line:90%
>> It's a curse.

00:11:06.600 --> 00:11:09.840 align:middle line:84%
On the one hand, you want
to show your artwork.

00:11:09.840 --> 00:11:12.840 align:middle line:84%
On the other hand, it's
just so difficult in a place

00:11:12.840 --> 00:11:18.180 align:middle line:84%
where there are no rules,
no laws, no police.

00:11:18.180 --> 00:11:21.585 align:middle line:84%
Solitude is a precious gift
that is becoming hard to find.

00:11:21.585 --> 00:11:27.990 align:middle line:90%


00:11:27.990 --> 00:11:31.150 align:middle line:84%
>> Being far from public sight
is also the goal of French

00:11:31.150 --> 00:11:33.397 align:middle line:90%
artist Jean Verame.

00:11:33.397 --> 00:11:34.230 align:middle line:90%
>> [SPEAKING FRENCH]

00:11:34.230 --> 00:11:37.020 align:middle line:84%
>> I'm not an exhibitionist,
so I go to desert places where

00:11:37.020 --> 00:11:38.820 align:middle line:90%
nobody goes.

00:11:38.820 --> 00:11:42.120 align:middle line:84%
>> In 1984, he too
was in Morocco,

00:11:42.120 --> 00:11:45.090 align:middle line:84%
several hundred kilometers
south of the "City of Orion,"

00:11:45.090 --> 00:11:48.120 align:middle line:84%
exploring a vast zone of
granite close to the Berber town

00:11:48.120 --> 00:11:49.050 align:middle line:90%
of Tafraoute.

00:11:49.050 --> 00:11:53.505 align:middle line:90%


00:11:53.505 --> 00:11:55.650 align:middle line:90%
