00:19:17.870 --> 00:19:19.910 align:middle line:90%
The landscape is his canvas.

00:19:19.910 --> 00:19:23.570 align:middle line:84%
His paints are made up
of plants and rocks.

00:19:23.570 --> 00:19:26.240 align:middle line:84%
>> He painted a tree that was
actually there in southern

00:19:26.240 --> 00:19:30.090 align:middle line:84%
France, and I'm reproducing
that tree with an actual plant.

00:19:30.090 --> 00:19:31.640 align:middle line:90%
So there was this Earth thing.

00:19:31.640 --> 00:19:33.150 align:middle line:90%
Van Gogh was all about nature.

00:19:33.150 --> 00:19:34.970 align:middle line:90%
He was all about living it.

00:19:34.970 --> 00:19:38.390 align:middle line:84%
He saw it in ways that
very few of us ever see it.

00:19:38.390 --> 00:19:41.090 align:middle line:84%
I felt like I got
a glimpse of how

00:19:41.090 --> 00:19:45.600 align:middle line:84%
he saw it by spending six
months recreating this piece.

00:19:45.600 --> 00:19:49.160 align:middle line:84%
>> A massive living earthwork
over 6,000 square meters

00:19:49.160 --> 00:19:50.270 align:middle line:90%
in size.

00:19:50.270 --> 00:19:52.940 align:middle line:84%
>> I lost 600 plants out of
the 1,000 that I planted,

00:19:52.940 --> 00:19:54.710 align:middle line:90%
and my oats didn't grow.

00:19:54.710 --> 00:19:57.080 align:middle line:84%
So I had to rethink
that, you know?

00:19:57.080 --> 00:19:59.150 align:middle line:90%
But you can't get mad about it.

00:19:59.150 --> 00:20:02.270 align:middle line:84%
You're working with nature,
with rain, with clouds,

00:20:02.270 --> 00:20:03.500 align:middle line:90%
with insects.

00:20:03.500 --> 00:20:06.560 align:middle line:84%
The deer came and ate all
of my squash one morning.

00:20:06.560 --> 00:20:17.310 align:middle line:90%


00:20:17.310 --> 00:20:19.930 align:middle line:84%
The camera and the plane
happened about the same time.

00:20:19.930 --> 00:20:24.840 align:middle line:84%
So there was this
incredible sensory overload,

00:20:24.840 --> 00:20:27.350 align:middle line:84%
looking at a planet
that we lived on forever

00:20:27.350 --> 00:20:28.950 align:middle line:90%
in a brand new way.

00:20:28.950 --> 00:20:31.260 align:middle line:84%
So land art was when
we discovered really

00:20:31.260 --> 00:20:34.334 align:middle line:84%
what it looked like
from above, and realized

00:20:34.334 --> 00:20:36.750 align:middle line:84%
that ancient people had been
creating things on the ground

00:20:36.750 --> 00:20:37.550 align:middle line:90%
forever.

00:20:37.550 --> 00:20:40.890 align:middle line:90%


00:20:40.890 --> 00:20:43.770 align:middle line:84%
>> Stan is deeply moved by
the works of Native American

00:20:43.770 --> 00:20:45.430 align:middle line:90%
Indians.

00:20:45.430 --> 00:20:48.600 align:middle line:84%
Their ancient engravings,
petroglyphs, and geoglyphs

00:20:48.600 --> 00:20:51.090 align:middle line:90%
have inspired him.

00:20:51.090 --> 00:20:53.160 align:middle line:84%
If their symbols
remain a mystery,

00:20:53.160 --> 00:20:56.700 align:middle line:84%
many works have a tendency to
bond human life with the Earth

00:20:56.700 --> 00:20:57.570 align:middle line:90%
and the universe.

00:20:57.570 --> 00:21:00.919 align:middle line:90%


00:21:00.919 --> 00:21:03.210 align:middle line:84%
>> The earthworks are kind
of guided by something else,

00:21:03.210 --> 00:21:04.010 align:middle line:90%
in a way.

00:21:04.010 --> 00:21:06.590 align:middle line:84%
And our life is, and
our art is certainly.

00:21:06.590 --> 00:21:08.240 align:middle line:90%
>> What is that something else?

00:21:08.240 --> 00:21:13.845 align:middle line:84%
>> Well, you know, it's probably
to me just an understanding

00:21:13.845 --> 00:21:16.300 align:middle line:84%
of how small we are
in the universe.

00:21:16.300 --> 00:21:21.210 align:middle line:90%


00:21:21.210 --> 00:21:25.380 align:middle line:84%
