00:22:48.070 --> 00:22:52.750 align:middle line:84%
>> People come out here and
they pray, they'll do songs,

00:22:52.750 --> 00:22:55.510 align:middle line:84%
they'll use this,
because I think this is--

00:22:55.510 --> 00:22:58.720 align:middle line:84%
we don't have a
chapel on campus.

00:22:58.720 --> 00:23:02.160 align:middle line:84%
This is the closest thing we
have to a chapel, you know,

00:23:02.160 --> 00:23:02.980 align:middle line:90%
is right here.

00:23:02.980 --> 00:23:13.400 align:middle line:90%


00:23:13.400 --> 00:23:16.370 align:middle line:84%
>> Stan Herd had the privilege
of approaching the mystical

00:23:16.370 --> 00:23:19.610 align:middle line:84%
and secret world of
native Indians of America,

00:23:19.610 --> 00:23:22.040 align:middle line:90%
a source of his inspiration.

00:23:22.040 --> 00:23:25.570 align:middle line:84%
>> The fact that I'm non-native
and that these people whom

00:23:25.570 --> 00:23:30.980 align:middle line:84%
my European ancestors kind
of trampled for 100 years,

00:23:30.980 --> 00:23:35.780 align:middle line:84%
and getting invited back to be
a part of this was very special.

00:23:35.780 --> 00:23:37.580 align:middle line:84%
And this ground that
we're standing on

00:23:37.580 --> 00:23:39.416 align:middle line:84%
is sacred, not because
of the artwork.

00:23:39.416 --> 00:23:41.040 align:middle line:84%
Because of the history
of these people.

00:23:41.040 --> 00:23:51.320 align:middle line:90%


00:23:51.320 --> 00:23:54.020 align:middle line:84%
If we have anything
to learn, we have

00:23:54.020 --> 00:23:56.900 align:middle line:84%
it to learn from
indigenous people who

00:23:56.900 --> 00:23:59.525 align:middle line:84%
have had this ancient
connection to the landscape.

00:23:59.525 --> 00:24:02.500 align:middle line:90%


00:24:02.500 --> 00:24:06.185 align:middle line:84%
A lot of it, I'm not even
really conscious of it.

00:24:06.185 --> 00:24:08.680 align:middle line:84%
It comes out, I put it on
the canvas, and I go, hmm.

00:24:08.680 --> 00:24:09.760 align:middle line:90%
I like that.

00:24:09.760 --> 00:24:12.610 align:middle line:84%
And later, I try
to figure out why,

00:24:12.610 --> 00:24:14.620 align:middle line:84%
and what the inspiration
was necessarily.

00:24:14.620 --> 00:24:16.590 align:middle line:90%
So I like that.

00:24:16.590 --> 00:24:18.010 align:middle line:90%
I like to get out of my way.

00:24:18.010 --> 00:24:25.282 align:middle line:90%


00:24:25.282 --> 00:24:27.240 align:middle line:84%
>> We're going to need,
like, a bunch of water.

00:24:27.240 --> 00:24:28.060 align:middle line:90%
>> Yeah.

00:24:28.060 --> 00:24:30.560 align:middle line:84%
>> Just a little bit of water's
not going to do anything.

00:24:30.560 --> 00:24:31.560 align:middle line:90%
>> Hopefully it'll rain.

00:24:31.560 --> 00:24:34.570 align:middle line:90%


00:24:34.570 --> 00:24:37.870 align:middle line:84%
To dance with nature,
you can't fight it.

00:24:37.870 --> 00:24:41.660 align:middle line:84%
You have to work in balance
with it to a certain extent.

00:24:41.660 --> 00:24:49.800 align:middle line:10%
It's an embrace of
nature, in a way.

00:24:49.800 --> 00:24:54.690 align:middle line:90%


00:24:54.690 --> 00:24:57.450 align:middle line:84%
I think people's lives
are changed a teeny bit

00:24:57.450 --> 00:25:00.140 align:middle line:84%
when they come to visit it,
because they find themselves

00:25:00.140 --> 00:25:00.940 align:middle line:90%
in it.

00:25:00.940 --> 00:25:06.780 align:middle line:84%
They It reveals their desire to
garden, to work with the land,

00:25:06.780 --> 00:25:08.160 align:middle line:90%
to get their hands in the soil.

00:25:08.160 --> 00:25:12.056 align:middle line:90%


00:25:12.056 --> 00:25:14.390 align:middle line:84%
>> And this is on her--
you said on her brooch?

00:25:14.390 --> 00:25:20.070 align:middle line:84%
>> This is-- you know,
it's near her hair.

00:25:20.070 --> 00:25:23.660 align:middle line:84%
>> To be able to sit inside
this artwork feels surreal.

00:25:23.660 --> 00:25:27.430 align:middle line:84%
It's not something
you can typically do.

00:25:27.430 --> 00:25:28.790 align:middle line:90%
This is not just dry paint.

00:25:28.790 --> 00:25:32.380 align:middle line:90%
This is a living organism.

00:25:32.380 --> 00:25:35.169 align:middle line:90%
Every plant has a soul.

00:25:35.169 --> 00:25:36.210 align:middle line:90%
The whole thing is alive.

00:25:36.210 --> 00:25:41.750 align:middle line:90%


00:25:41.750 --> 00:25:44.450 align:middle line:84%
>> Sometimes mysterious
things happen.

00:25:44.450 --> 00:25:48.170 align:middle line:84%
Plants grow up that I wasn't
expecting that change of color,

00:25:48.170 --> 00:25:49.790 align:middle line:90%
and I like it.

00:25:49.790 --> 00:25:50.820 align:middle line:90%
Sometimes I hate it.

00:25:50.820 --> 00:25:51.620 align:middle line:90%
[LAUGH]

00:25:51.620 --> 00:25:56.090 align:middle line:84%
So I never really know
what I'm going to get.

00:25:56.090 --> 00:25:58.362 align:middle line:90%
And oftentimes, I'm surprised.

00:25:58.362 --> 00:26:07.040 align:middle line:90%


00:26:07.040 --> 00:26:10.810 align:middle line:84%
>> French artist Michel Granger
is also in the representational

00:26:10.810 --> 00:26:12.652 align:middle line:90%
art movement.

00:26:12.652 --> 00:26:14.990 align:middle line:84%
He is world famous
for his paintings that

00:26:14.990 --> 00:26:17.930 align:middle line:84%
illustrate magazine
covers, posters, stamps,

00:26:17.930 --> 00:26:18.830 align:middle line:90%
and record covers.

00:26:18.830 --> 00:26:19.663 align:middle line:90%
>> [SPEAKING FRENCH]

00:26:19.663 --> 00:26:21.530 align:middle line:90%
>> The original was like this.

00:26:21.530 --> 00:26:23.870 align:middle line:84%
>> He reproduced a
land art version of one

00:26:23.870 --> 00:26:27.020 align:middle line:84%
of the spectators in his
masterpiece "Stage Fright"

00:26:27.020 --> 00:26:29.270 align:middle line:84%
from the cover of
the album "Équinoxe"

00:26:29.270 --> 00:26:31.560 align:middle line:90%
by Jean-Michel Jarre.

00:26:31.560 --> 00:26:32.780 align:middle line:90%
>> [SPEAKING FRENCH]

00:26:32.780 --> 00:26:34.460 align:middle line:10%
>> I imagine the
author, the singer,

00:26:34.460 --> 00:26:37.490 align:middle line:10%
or the musician standing on
stage, looking at the audience,

00:26:37.490 --> 00:26:40.280 align:middle line:10%
