a pair of binoculars like this.

00:26:40.280 --> 00:26:41.810 align:middle line:90%
Wouldn't it be imposing?

00:26:41.810 --> 00:26:44.180 align:middle line:84%
An audience without binoculars
is pretty impressive,

00:26:44.180 --> 00:26:47.439 align:middle line:84%
but close up like that, it's
probably highly emotional.

00:26:47.439 --> 00:26:53.710 align:middle line:90%


00:26:53.710 --> 00:26:56.800 align:middle line:84%
>> Both size and color of the
original painting were to be

00:26:56.800 --> 00:26:59.350 align:middle line:84%
forgotten for the
land art experience.

00:26:59.350 --> 00:27:00.880 align:middle line:90%
Landscape and dimension.

00:27:00.880 --> 00:27:02.920 align:middle line:84%
Green was the new
dominant shade.

00:27:02.920 --> 00:27:06.100 align:middle line:84%
For the land art experience,
Michel Granger chose a spot

00:27:06.100 --> 00:27:09.900 align:middle line:84%
at an aerodrome close
to the town of Bezançon.

00:27:09.900 --> 00:27:12.705 align:middle line:84%
>> It's several
football fields in size.

00:27:12.705 --> 00:27:16.180 align:middle line:84%
We leave the traditional
canvas for a new dimension, one

00:27:16.180 --> 00:27:17.800 align:middle line:90%
that planet Earth gives us.

00:27:17.800 --> 00:27:19.780 align:middle line:90%
It isn't infinite, but could be.

00:27:19.780 --> 00:27:23.500 align:middle line:84%
We probably could make
an infinite land art.

00:27:23.500 --> 00:27:26.840 align:middle line:84%
>> The secret to his shades of
green lies in the height of his

00:27:26.840 --> 00:27:28.787 align:middle line:90%
mowing.

00:27:28.787 --> 00:27:29.620 align:middle line:90%
>> [SPEAKING FRENCH]

00:27:29.620 --> 00:27:32.650 align:middle line:84%
>> When the grass is high,
we get a dark green color.

00:27:32.650 --> 00:27:35.260 align:middle line:84%
When it's short, we
get a garden green.

00:27:35.260 --> 00:27:37.030 align:middle line:84%
If we cut the grass
even more, the green

00:27:37.030 --> 00:27:38.410 align:middle line:90%
becomes closer to the surface.

00:27:38.410 --> 00:27:44.170 align:middle line:90%


00:27:44.170 --> 00:27:45.030 align:middle line:90%
>> [SPEAKING FRENCH]

00:27:45.030 --> 00:27:47.238 align:middle line:84%
>> It's really interesting,
because the grass becomes

00:27:47.238 --> 00:27:48.800 align:middle line:90%
a pictorial element.

00:27:48.800 --> 00:27:51.630 align:middle line:84%
And just by working with grass,
mowing at different heights,

00:27:51.630 --> 00:27:54.640 align:middle line:84%
it produces a variety of
different shades of green.

00:27:54.640 --> 00:27:59.005 align:middle line:90%


00:27:59.005 --> 00:28:00.770 align:middle line:90%
>> [SPEAKING FRENCH]

00:28:00.770 --> 00:28:03.240 align:middle line:84%
>> I wanted to reproduce a
member of the audience from

00:28:03.240 --> 00:28:05.770 align:middle line:84%
the "Stage Fright
Équinoxe" painting,

00:28:05.770 --> 00:28:09.090 align:middle line:84%
someone looking through
a pair of binoculars.

00:28:09.090 --> 00:28:11.630 align:middle line:84%
Imagine a small plane
approaching the aerodrome,

00:28:11.630 --> 00:28:14.550 align:middle line:84%
its occupants looking down
and seeing this huge image

00:28:14.550 --> 00:28:16.560 align:middle line:84%
on the ground that is
looking back up at them

00:28:16.560 --> 00:28:18.000 align:middle line:90%
through a pair of binoculars.

00:28:18.000 --> 00:28:23.030 align:middle line:90%


00:28:23.030 --> 00:28:26.450 align:middle line:84%
>> This style of land art is
similar to crop circles that

00:28:26.450 --> 00:28:32.310 align:middle line:84%
appear in fields during
the summer months,

00:28:32.310 --> 00:28:33.930 align:middle line:90%
and in snow during the winter.

00:28:33.930 --> 00:28:37.290 align:middle line:90%


00:28:37.290 --> 00:28:40.860 align:middle line:84%
Over the past few years, ski
stations all over the world

00:28:40.860 --> 00:28:43.890 align:middle line:84%
are requesting this
new style of land art.

00:28:43.890 --> 00:28:46.260 align:middle line:84%
To create these
original tracks, no need

00:28:46.260 --> 00:28:51.570 align:middle line:84%
to know how to ski, but to
walk in style, British style.

00:28:51.570 --> 00:28:53.810 align:middle line:84%
>> I was always mad
about mountains,

00:28:53.810 --> 00:28:56.820 align:middle line:84%
and when you've got
mountain combined with snow,

00:28:56.820 --> 00:28:58.620 align:middle line:90%
it makes them even better.

00:28:58.620 --> 00:28:59.750 align:middle line:90%
I just like snow a lot.

00:28:59.750 --> 00:29:00.870 align:middle line:90%
I like its texture.

00:29:00.870 --> 00:29:03.161 align:middle line:84%
And the simple fact that you
can draw a line through it

00:29:03.161 --> 00:29:06.210 align:middle line:84%
so easily just by
walking through it.

00:29:06.210 --> 00:29:09.000 align:middle line:84%
>> An orienteering and
geometrical enthusiast,

00:29:09.000 --> 00:29:11.970 align:middle line:84%
Simon Beck swapped his
life as an Oxford-qualified

00:29:11.970 --> 00:29:15.375 align:middle line:84%
cartographer to carry out his
hobby in solidarity artwork.

00:29:15.375 --> 00:29:19.484 align:middle line:90%


00:29:19.484 --> 00:29:23.310 align:middle line:84%
>> Never quite as easy as
you think, getting these on.

00:29:23.310 --> 00:29:25.900 align:middle line:84%
>> His art requires the
combination of three key

00:29:25.900 --> 00:29:26.700 align:middle line:90%
elements.

00:29:26.700 --> 00:29:30.760 align:middle line:84%
Fresh snow, blue skies,
and little or no wind.

00:29:30.760 --> 00:29:34.560 align:middle line:84%
At Les Arc ski station, Simon
has spotted an ideal sight

00:29:34.560 --> 00:29:38.970 align:middle line:84%
at an altitude of 2,500
meters, a frozen lake covered

00:29:38.970 --> 00:29:42.890 align:middle line:84%
in a thick layer of powder snow,
