00:29:42.890 --> 00:29:44.880 align:middle line:90%
of one and a half hectares.

00:29:44.880 --> 00:29:47.400 align:middle line:84%
It is 8:00 AM, and
Simon is alone.

00:29:47.400 --> 00:29:50.100 align:middle line:84%
He places his first
markers using a compass

00:29:50.100 --> 00:29:51.520 align:middle line:90%
and counting his steps.

00:29:51.520 --> 00:29:54.090 align:middle line:84%
Here he cannot rub
out any mistakes.

00:29:54.090 --> 00:30:01.754 align:middle line:84%
>> Two, three, four,
five, six, seven.

00:30:01.754 --> 00:30:02.554 align:middle line:90%
Oops.

00:30:02.554 --> 00:30:05.476 align:middle line:90%


00:30:05.476 --> 00:30:06.937 align:middle line:90%
Oh.

00:30:06.937 --> 00:30:08.530 align:middle line:90%
Oh, well.

00:30:08.530 --> 00:30:10.060 align:middle line:84%
When you make a
booboo, what you do

00:30:10.060 --> 00:30:13.270 align:middle line:84%
is you change the design
so it looks right.

00:30:13.270 --> 00:30:14.230 align:middle line:90%
[LAUGH]

00:30:14.230 --> 00:30:15.670 align:middle line:90%
Yeah, I should have curved left.

00:30:15.670 --> 00:30:18.310 align:middle line:10%
I curved right.

00:30:18.310 --> 00:30:22.130 align:middle line:10%
I'm not quite the
right shape now.

00:30:22.130 --> 00:30:22.930 align:middle line:90%
Never mind.

00:30:22.930 --> 00:30:26.291 align:middle line:90%


00:30:26.291 --> 00:30:30.425 align:middle line:84%
We'll do all of
them curving right.

00:30:30.425 --> 00:30:33.060 align:middle line:84%
You reproduce that mistake six
times throughout the drawing,

00:30:33.060 --> 00:30:34.560 align:middle line:84%
and then it looked
like it was meant

00:30:34.560 --> 00:30:37.360 align:middle line:90%
to be there in the first place.

00:30:37.360 --> 00:30:39.360 align:middle line:84%
Drawings don't always end
up how they originally

00:30:39.360 --> 00:30:42.900 align:middle line:90%
were planned to be.

00:30:42.900 --> 00:30:47.455 align:middle line:84%
>> The sun isn't up yet, and the
tracks are already in danger.

00:30:47.455 --> 00:30:50.150 align:middle line:90%
>> It's blowing a bit.

00:30:50.150 --> 00:30:51.420 align:middle line:90%
It might spoil the drawing.

00:30:51.420 --> 00:30:54.880 align:middle line:84%
I don't think it's going
to wreck the drawing.

00:30:54.880 --> 00:30:58.240 align:middle line:84%
>> Simon always starts out his
land art by placing several

00:30:58.240 --> 00:31:03.010 align:middle line:84%
equidistant markers that
will be linked by foot.

00:31:03.010 --> 00:31:05.380 align:middle line:90%
>> Here comes the sun.

00:31:05.380 --> 00:31:12.940 align:middle line:90%
Dun, dun, dun, da-dun!

00:31:12.940 --> 00:31:17.200 align:middle line:84%
Bam, bam, bam, bam, bam,
bam, bam, bam, bam, bam, bam.

00:31:17.200 --> 00:31:26.740 align:middle line:90%


00:31:26.740 --> 00:31:30.100 align:middle line:84%
>> In today's society of
sophisticated technology,

00:31:30.100 --> 00:31:34.210 align:middle line:84%
Simon does without a
computer, GPS, or sat nav,

00:31:34.210 --> 00:31:35.680 align:middle line:90%
and always works alone.

00:31:35.680 --> 00:31:41.990 align:middle line:90%


00:31:41.990 --> 00:31:44.360 align:middle line:84%
The drawing is
memorized in his head.

00:31:44.360 --> 00:31:57.730 align:middle line:90%


00:31:57.730 --> 00:32:01.950 align:middle line:84%
>> Land art is a combination
with something created

00:32:01.950 --> 00:32:08.070 align:middle line:84%
by an artist and what already
is in place, be that the trees,

00:32:08.070 --> 00:32:11.500 align:middle line:84%
the fields, the mountains,
the surroundings.

00:32:11.500 --> 00:32:15.390 align:middle line:84%
So the two are like a
team, acting in symbiosis

00:32:15.390 --> 00:32:16.830 align:middle line:90%
to complement each other.

00:32:16.830 --> 00:32:18.957 align:middle line:84%
And so the whole
result is better

00:32:18.957 --> 00:32:20.040 align:middle line:90%
than the sum of the parts.

00:32:20.040 --> 00:32:23.350 align:middle line:90%


00:32:23.350 --> 00:32:26.740 align:middle line:84%
>> The striking precision of
each of Simon Beck's footsteps

00:32:26.740 --> 00:32:29.530 align:middle line:84%
is what makes this
giant piece of snow art.

00:32:29.530 --> 00:32:32.990 align:middle line:90%


00:32:32.990 --> 00:32:36.500 align:middle line:84%
>> The Eskimos apparently have
70 different words for snow,

00:32:36.500 --> 00:32:39.750 align:middle line:84%
and they write for lots and
lots of different kinds of snow.

00:32:39.750 --> 00:32:43.550 align:middle line:90%


