I mean, snow is so expert at
getting where it isn't wanted.

00:34:50.389 --> 00:34:53.510 align:middle line:84%
>> Night has set in, and the
temperature is minus 10 degrees

00:34:53.510 --> 00:34:54.739 align:middle line:90%
centigrade.

00:34:54.739 --> 00:34:57.080 align:middle line:84%
Alone and exhausted,
Simon is set

00:34:57.080 --> 00:34:59.630 align:middle line:84%
on finishing his task
in the dark in the hope

00:34:59.630 --> 00:35:03.070 align:middle line:84%
that he can take a
photo the next morning.

00:35:03.070 --> 00:35:06.150 align:middle line:84%
He must get his shot on
camera before fresh snowflakes

00:35:06.150 --> 00:35:07.330 align:middle line:90%
cover it up forever.

00:35:07.330 --> 00:35:11.150 align:middle line:90%


00:35:11.150 --> 00:35:13.310 align:middle line:84%
As the night settles
in the French Alps,

00:35:13.310 --> 00:35:15.760 align:middle line:90%
a new day begins in California.

00:35:15.760 --> 00:35:21.640 align:middle line:90%
[MUSIC PLAYING]

00:35:21.640 --> 00:35:22.630 align:middle line:90%


00:35:22.630 --> 00:35:26.620 align:middle line:84%
Andres Amador is on the
lookout for a new workplace.

00:35:26.620 --> 00:35:30.910 align:middle line:10%
>> What I'm looking for
for my artwork is space,

00:35:30.910 --> 00:35:32.960 align:middle line:10%
as much as I can have.

00:35:32.960 --> 00:35:33.760 align:middle line:90%
And flatness.

00:35:33.760 --> 00:35:38.930 align:middle line:90%


00:35:38.930 --> 00:35:42.620 align:middle line:84%
I can only do my
artwork during low tide.

00:35:42.620 --> 00:35:44.960 align:middle line:84%
And so that depends
upon the cycles

00:35:44.960 --> 00:35:51.660 align:middle line:84%
of the moon and the Earth,
and every day it changes.

00:35:51.660 --> 00:35:53.370 align:middle line:84%
And every day, my
canvas changes.

00:35:53.370 --> 00:36:11.060 align:middle line:90%


00:36:11.060 --> 00:36:13.940 align:middle line:84%
>> Andres has dedicated
his life to sand art,

00:36:13.940 --> 00:36:21.110 align:middle line:84%
the creation of land art
on the beach, since 2004.

00:36:21.110 --> 00:36:23.600 align:middle line:84%
>> Almost every beach has
a different type of sand.

00:36:23.600 --> 00:36:28.220 align:middle line:84%
And the sand here in San
Diego has been very fine

00:36:28.220 --> 00:36:30.500 align:middle line:84%
and has been perfect
for the artwork,

00:36:30.500 --> 00:36:32.615 align:middle line:84%
because it holds
moisture very well.

00:36:32.615 --> 00:36:34.430 align:middle line:90%
It doesn't dry out too quickly.

00:36:34.430 --> 00:36:36.390 align:middle line:84%
But then at the same
time, it's very compact,

00:36:36.390 --> 00:36:40.100 align:middle line:84%
so you have to push a lot
harder to get the rake to dig in

00:36:40.100 --> 00:36:41.960 align:middle line:90%
deep enough to make the mark.

00:36:41.960 --> 00:36:47.810 align:middle line:90%


00:36:47.810 --> 00:36:49.400 align:middle line:90%
I make mistakes all the time.

00:36:49.400 --> 00:36:54.630 align:middle line:90%


00:36:54.630 --> 00:37:01.370 align:middle line:84%
So then I have to improvise
and keep it together somehow.

00:37:01.370 --> 00:37:10.562 align:middle line:90%


00:37:10.562 --> 00:37:12.770 align:middle line:84%
>> How do you create something
that's so big that you

00:37:12.770 --> 00:37:14.797 align:middle line:90%
can't see, and you're inside of?

00:37:14.797 --> 00:37:16.130 align:middle line:90%
How do you keep it all together?

00:37:16.130 --> 00:37:19.266 align:middle line:90%


00:37:19.266 --> 00:37:21.750 align:middle line:84%
And this is showing
one way, which

00:37:21.750 --> 00:37:24.150 align:middle line:84%
is to create kind
of linear grid,

00:37:24.150 --> 00:37:28.211 align:middle line:84%
and then I can start to
fill it in with these kind

00:37:28.211 --> 00:37:29.150 align:middle line:90%
of blocky shapes.

00:37:29.150 --> 00:37:32.951 align:middle line:90%


00:37:32.951 --> 00:37:34.950 align:middle line:84%
People, when they're
walking by, were asking me,

00:37:34.950 --> 00:37:35.700 align:middle line:90%
what does it mean?

00:37:35.700 --> 00:37:36.616 align:middle line:90%
Does it say something?

00:37:36.616 --> 00:37:38.525 align:middle line:90%
And it looks like a language.

00:37:38.525 --> 00:37:39.690 align:middle line:90%
So I was like, cool.

00:37:39.690 --> 00:37:42.210 align:middle line:90%
That's kind of the thought.

00:37:42.210 --> 00:37:44.130 align:middle line:84%
Every culture seems
to have its way

00:37:44.130 --> 00:37:49.140 align:middle line:84%
of writing that looks
like drawing that is just

00:37:49.140 --> 00:37:52.330 align:middle line:90%
like some alien language.

00:37:52.330 --> 00:37:55.270 align:middle line:90%


00:37:55.270 --> 00:37:57.310 align:middle line:84%
This piece is
inspired by carvings

00:37:57.310 --> 00:38:02.530 align:middle line:84%
on rocks called petroglyphs,
done by cultures

00:38:02.530 --> 00:38:04.630 align:middle line:90%
thousands of years ago.

00:38:04.630 --> 00:38:08.350 align:middle line:84%
And it has a feeling like this
has been carved into the beach.

00:38:08.350 --> 00:38:21.600 align:middle line:90%


00:38:21.600 --> 00:38:23.850 align:middle line:90%
This took longer than expected.

00:38:23.850 --> 00:38:25.770 align:middle line:90%
It was more complex.

00:38:25.770 --> 00:38:31.800 align:middle line:84%
I didn't get as far as I wanted
to, so I wanted to go bigger,

00:38:31.800 --> 00:38:33.450 align:middle line:84%
and I wanted to
at least complete

00:38:33.450 --> 00:38:36.060 align:middle line:84%
going down into the
water before the sun set.

00:38:36.060 --> 00:38:37.720 align:middle line:90%
So I didn't make that goal.

00:38:37.720 --> 00:38:40.090 align:middle line:90%
But it feels good.

00:38:40.090 --> 00:38:42.860 align:middle line:84%
I mean, I think it
looks really good.

00:38:42.860 --> 00:38:47.330 align:middle line:84%
>> This giant piece of artwork
measures over 150 meters long

00:38:47.330 --> 00:38:49.865 align:middle line:90%
and eight meters wide.

00:38:49.865 --> 00:38:51.990 align:middle line:84%
>> So I'm just going to do
this last part that goes

00:38:51.990 --> 00:38:55.790 align:middle line:84%
into the water, and
then I can step away.

00:38:55.790 --> 00:38:56.590 align:middle line:90%
And

00:38:56.590 --> 00:39:00.260 align:middle line:84%
>> Ephemeral is, as always,
the rule of the game.

00:39:00.260 --> 00:39:03.210 align:middle line:84%
Andres will not have time to
capture his completed work

00:39:03.210 --> 00:39:05.730 align:middle line:84%
on camera as the tide
will clear the beach

00:39:05.730 --> 00:39:07.247 align:middle line:90%
in the darkness of the night.

00:39:07.247 --> 00:39:16.030 align:middle line:90%


00:39:16.030 --> 00:39:17.950 align:middle line:84%
Back in the French
Alps, the night

00:39:17.950 --> 00:39:20.800 align:middle line:84%
was short for Simon Beck,
who returned to his studio.

00:39:20.800 --> 00:39:23.660 align:middle line:90%


00:39:23.660 --> 00:39:26.210 align:middle line:84%
He's impatient to capture
his work on camera,

00:39:26.210 --> 00:39:28.370 align:middle line:84%
the ultimate step that
will enable his effort

00:39:28.370 --> 00:39:32.010 align:middle line:90%
to be immortalized and shared.

00:39:32.010 --> 00:39:33.850 align:middle line:84%
He worked a fair
part of the night,

00:39:33.850 --> 00:39:37.090 align:middle line:84%
but just what are his limits
in such difficult conditions?

00:39:37.090 --> 00:39:40.720 align:middle line:84%
>> You draw until you're too
tired to carry on drawing.

00:39:40.720 --> 00:39:43.140 align:middle line:84%
So the limiting factor
is not how long it takes.

00:39:43.140 --> 00:39:45.670 align:middle line:84%
It's how much you can do
before you get too tired.

00:39:45.670 --> 00:39:47.290 align:middle line:84%
The greatest danger
of doing a drawing

00:39:47.290 --> 00:39:49.690 align:middle line:84%
is simply hypothermia,
getting too tired

00:39:49.690 --> 00:39:52.600 align:middle line:84%
and grinding to a halt.
And if you got too tired,

00:39:52.600 --> 00:39:56.780 align:middle line:84%
you basically sit down
in the snow and die.

00:39:56.780 --> 00:39:58.910 align:middle line:84%
You see that pattern
in the snow now?

00:39:58.910 --> 00:40:03.020 align:middle line:84%
You can see the remains
of an old drawing.

00:40:03.020 --> 00:40:07.220 align:middle line:84%
>> Simon climbs to an altitude
of 2,700 meters to get a good

00:40:07.220 --> 00:40:08.330 align:middle line:90%
sight at his creation.

00:40:08.330 --> 00:40:11.480 align:middle line:90%


00:40:11.480 --> 00:40:14.370 align:middle line:84%
>> This is the big moment,
when you see the drawing

00:40:14.370 --> 00:40:16.244 align:middle line:90%
for the first time.

00:40:16.244 --> 00:40:17.910 align:middle line:84%
There's always a
feeling of anticipation

00:40:17.910 --> 00:40:22.440 align:middle line:84%
as you get out of the lift
here and walk over to the edge.

00:40:22.440 --> 00:40:24.830 align:middle line:90%
And there it is.

00:40:24.830 --> 00:40:29.565 align:middle line:84%
Well, I can genuinely say
that is actually better

00:40:29.565 --> 00:40:31.180 align:middle line:90%
than I expected.

00:40:31.180 --> 00:40:33.976 align:middle line:90%
I'm quite pleased with that.

00:40:33.976 --> 00:40:35.725 align:middle line:84%
Looks so good from
here with that mountain

00:40:35.725 --> 00:40:37.146 align:middle line:90%
in the background.

00:40:37.146 --> 00:40:45.040 align:middle line:90%


00:40:45.040 --> 00:40:46.260 align:middle line:90%
It is not ephemeral.

00:40:46.260 --> 00:40:48.090 align:middle line:90%
Now we've got photography.

00:40:48.090 --> 00:40:50.610 align:middle line:84%
Most people will only ever see
the majority of the world's

00:40:50.610 --> 00:40:53.040 align:middle line:90%
artworks as photographs.

00:40:53.040 --> 00:40:56.770 align:middle line:84%
So it's not the real
thing, of course.

00:40:56.770 --> 00:40:59.240 align:middle line:84%
But the other way to
answer that question

00:40:59.240 --> 00:41:03.030 align:middle line:84%
is to look at the situation we'd
have if it was not ephemeral.

00:41:03.030 --> 00:41:04.950 align:middle line:84%
Every possible place
you can draw something

00:41:04.950 --> 00:41:09.220 align:middle line:84%
would be covered in graffiti
of one sort or another.

00:41:09.220 --> 00:41:10.930 align:middle line:84%
>> Depending on
weather conditions,

00:41:10.930 --> 00:41:14.350 align:middle line:84%
Simon creates roughly 40
landscapes each winter.

00:41:14.350 --> 00:41:18.810 align:middle line:84%
His art requires a sharp
mind and a trained body.

00:41:18.810 --> 00:41:20.790 align:middle line:84%
>> You can argue over
how much is mathematics,

00:41:20.790 --> 00:41:23.700 align:middle line:84%
how much is geometry,
how much is art?

00:41:23.700 --> 00:41:25.170 align:middle line:90%
There's a bit of all three.

00:41:25.170 --> 00:41:27.570 align:middle line:90%
Most of it is done indoors.

00:41:27.570 --> 00:41:29.490 align:middle line:84%
When you're outdoors,
it's a question

00:41:29.490 --> 00:41:32.705 align:middle line:84%
of putting your drawing
on paper and changing it

00:41:32.705 --> 00:41:33.830 align:middle line:90%
into a drawing in the snow.

00:41:33.830 --> 00:41:36.840 align:middle line:90%


00:41:36.840 --> 00:41:39.360 align:middle line:10%
You never quite know how it's
going to turn out, though,

00:41:39.360 --> 00:41:42.780 align:middle line:10%
so there's always a certain
amount of uncertainty in it.

00:41:42.780 --> 00:41:44.830 align:middle line:84%
Occasionally, somebody
will ask, what is it?

00:41:44.830 --> 00:41:47.970 align:middle line:84%
It isn't really meant to be
anything in the real world.

00:41:47.970 --> 00:41:52.080 align:middle line:84%
It's just a rather
attractive geometric pattern.

00:41:52.080 --> 00:42:05.472 align:middle line:90%


00:42:05.472 --> 00:42:07.510 align:middle line:84%
>> I think it's
absolutely beautiful.

00:42:07.510 --> 00:42:10.176 align:middle line:84%
It's brilliant, because you just
sort of come around the corner,

00:42:10.176 --> 00:42:12.430 align:middle line:84%
and suddenly you can
just see it in the snow.

00:42:12.430 --> 00:42:12.740 align:middle line:90%
>> [SPEAKING FOREIGN LANGUAGE]

00:42:12.740 --> 00:42:13.790 align:middle line:90%
>> It's magnificent.

00:42:13.790 --> 00:42:14.920 align:middle line:90%
What does it inspire?

00:42:14.920 --> 00:42:17.266 align:middle line:84%
Curiosity, because we
don't know how he does it.

00:42:17.266 --> 00:42:18.640 align:middle line:84%
>> I think he does
it by walking.

00:42:18.640 --> 00:42:20.600 align:middle line:90%
>> Is that-- really?

00:42:20.600 --> 00:42:21.650 align:middle line:90%
Wow.

00:42:21.650 --> 00:42:22.900 align:middle line:90%
>> [SPEAKING FOREIGN LANGUAGE]

00:42:22.900 --> 00:42:25.390 align:middle line:84%
>> How on Earth can he draw
such a perfect geometric form

00:42:25.390 --> 00:42:27.280 align:middle line:90%
by foot?

00:42:27.280 --> 00:42:29.020 align:middle line:90%
It's baffling.

00:42:29.020 --> 00:42:29.820 align:middle line:90%
>> He's an artist.

00:42:29.820 --> 00:42:31.390 align:middle line:90%
He needs to express himself.

00:42:31.390 --> 00:42:34.462 align:middle line:84%
>> I suppose you could
call it tag snow.

00:42:34.462 --> 00:42:37.690 align:middle line:84%
>> And that is how the visitors
of the day nicknamed Simon

00:42:37.690 --> 00:42:38.490 align:middle line:90%
Beck.

00:42:38.490 --> 00:42:40.971 align:middle line:84%
Tag snow, the man
who tags the snow.

00:42:40.971 --> 00:42:45.790 align:middle line:90%


00:42:45.790 --> 00:42:48.897 align:middle line:84%
>> I'd love to have enough
money to fund a team of people

00:42:48.897 --> 00:42:50.980 align:middle line:84%
to come out and help me
make a really big drawing.

00:42:50.980 --> 00:42:51.780 align:middle line:90%
That is my dream.

00:42:51.780 --> 00:43:01.820 align:middle line:90%


00:43:01.820 --> 00:43:05.180 align:middle line:84%
>> Back to California where
Andres Amador is doing just

00:43:05.180 --> 00:43:08.710 align:middle line:84%
that, directing a team to
create a new collective form

00:43:08.710 --> 00:43:09.510 align:middle line:90%
of artwork.

00:43:09.510 --> 00:43:12.200 align:middle line:90%
>> Inhale from the Earth.

00:43:12.200 --> 00:43:16.070 align:middle line:84%
And exhale, forward
roll down to the ground,

00:43:16.070 --> 00:43:17.440 align:middle line:90%
touching the ground.

00:43:17.440 --> 00:43:23.210 align:middle line:84%
And then inhale, slowly
rolling up from the Earth.

00:43:23.210 --> 00:43:24.860 align:middle line:90%
Bring the energy up.

00:43:24.860 --> 00:43:27.815 align:middle line:84%
And exhale, reaching up to the
sky, pushing energy to the sky.

00:43:27.815 --> 00:43:32.030 align:middle line:90%


00:43:32.030 --> 00:43:34.980 align:middle line:84%
And at first, I called
them the prayer artworks,

00:43:34.980 --> 00:43:38.100 align:middle line:84%
because it really felt like
I was engaging in a living

00:43:38.100 --> 00:43:42.210 align:middle line:90%
prayer, a prayer in action.

00:43:42.210 --> 00:43:46.170 align:middle line:84%
But prayer feels very
religious, and what I'm doing

00:43:46.170 --> 00:43:47.640 align:middle line:90%
is not about religion.

00:43:47.640 --> 00:43:49.650 align:middle line:84%
I would say it's about
spirituality in the sense

00:43:49.650 --> 00:43:56.190 align:middle line:84%
that it is about how we can
engage life at a deeper level,

00:43:56.190 --> 00:43:59.560 align:middle line:84%
at a higher level, at a
more fulfilling level.

00:43:59.560 --> 00:44:03.150 align:middle line:90%


00:44:03.150 --> 00:44:03.950 align:middle line:90%
>> Start to lift.

00:44:03.950 --> 00:44:08.740 align:middle line:84%
Lift, lift, lift,
lift, lift, lift.

00:44:08.740 --> 00:44:09.540 align:middle line:90%
See?

00:44:09.540 --> 00:44:10.850 align:middle line:90%
It is kind of a strenuous job.

00:44:10.850 --> 00:44:12.475 align:middle line:84%
See how you're still
make a deep gouge?

00:44:12.475 --> 00:44:13.980 align:middle line:90%
>> It's still too deep.

00:44:13.980 --> 00:44:16.740 align:middle line:84%
>> They start out by tracing
outlines for the principle

00:44:16.740 --> 00:44:19.270 align:middle line:90%
heavy shadings.

00:44:19.270 --> 00:44:22.685 align:middle line:84%
On the beach, only the
deeper marks will be seen.

00:44:22.685 --> 00:44:25.312 align:middle line:84%
Light footprints will be
invisible from the sky.

00:44:25.312 --> 00:44:28.410 align:middle line:90%


00:44:28.410 --> 00:44:29.220 align:middle line:90%
How is that going?

00:44:29.220 --> 00:44:30.145 align:middle line:90%
Does that feel OK?

00:44:30.145 --> 00:44:30.560 align:middle line:90%
>> Yeah.

00:44:30.560 --> 00:44:31.590 align:middle line:84%
>> Would you do
more on this one?

00:44:31.590 --> 00:44:32.390 align:middle line:90%
>> Sure.

00:44:32.390 --> 00:44:33.330 align:middle line:90%
Same technique.

00:44:33.330 --> 00:44:34.600 align:middle line:90%
>> Same thing.

00:44:34.600 --> 00:44:35.400 align:middle line:90%
OK.

00:44:35.400 --> 00:44:37.290 align:middle line:84%
To Ron, I'm going to
have you do spirals.

00:44:37.290 --> 00:44:54.300 align:middle line:90%


00:44:54.300 --> 00:44:57.610 align:middle line:84%
Even with myself, I need to be
able to let go of the result.

00:44:57.610 --> 00:45:01.530 align:middle line:10%
But even more so when I
do it with anyone else,

00:45:01.530 --> 00:45:07.032 align:middle line:10%
I'll have the desire to
have it be a certain way.

00:45:07.032 --> 00:45:11.050 align:middle line:84%
And people interpret what
I'm saying differently.

00:45:11.050 --> 00:45:14.645 align:middle line:90%
They have different abilities.

00:45:14.645 --> 00:45:16.020 align:middle line:84%
Those can be
moments where I have

00:45:16.020 --> 00:45:19.185 align:middle line:84%
to remember that all
things are impermanent.

00:45:19.185 --> 00:45:33.550 align:middle line:90%


00:45:33.550 --> 00:45:35.950 align:middle line:84%
>> The first impression
is startling,

00:45:35.950 --> 00:45:38.830 align:middle line:84%
and reveals a
promising creation.

00:45:38.830 --> 00:45:45.340 align:middle line:84%
Andres Amador is a master
of the art, sand art.

00:45:45.340 --> 00:45:48.490 align:middle line:84%
>> I want to do another layer,
because the water's receded out

00:45:48.490 --> 00:45:50.200 align:middle line:84%
enough that we
can do a few more.

00:45:50.200 --> 00:45:53.070 align:middle line:84%
It'll kind of fade
into the back there.

00:45:53.070 --> 00:45:53.870 align:middle line:90%
That's cool.

00:45:53.870 --> 00:46:00.430 align:middle line:90%


00:46:00.430 --> 00:46:03.220 align:middle line:84%
>> Once you get your
moves and you get into it,

00:46:03.220 --> 00:46:04.590 align:middle line:90%
it's literally a dance.

00:46:04.590 --> 00:46:06.160 align:middle line:90%
It's-- not-- It was so good.

00:46:06.160 --> 00:46:10.560 align:middle line:84%
It's like in between
painting, dancing,

00:46:10.560 --> 00:46:13.080 align:middle line:90%
and some sort of Tai Chi.

00:46:13.080 --> 00:46:14.190 align:middle line:90%
It's beautiful.

00:46:14.190 --> 00:46:16.300 align:middle line:90%
It literally puts you in a flow.

00:46:16.300 --> 00:46:17.100 align:middle line:90%
I loved it.

00:46:17.100 --> 00:46:22.020 align:middle line:90%


00:46:22.020 --> 00:46:26.297 align:middle line:84%
We're going to, I think,
come together in the center,

00:46:26.297 --> 00:46:27.630 align:middle line:90%
or as close to center as we can.

00:46:27.630 --> 00:46:30.120 align:middle line:84%
And the petals layer
from the center.

00:46:30.120 --> 00:46:33.018 align:middle line:84%
And I'll do, like, a zoom
back and do a picture.

00:46:33.018 --> 00:46:41.250 align:middle line:90%


00:46:41.250 --> 00:46:44.430 align:middle line:84%
When I do my art,
the people who see it

00:46:44.430 --> 00:46:47.220 align:middle line:90%
are affected in some way.

00:46:47.220 --> 00:46:49.620 align:middle line:90%
And they're going to go out.

00:46:49.620 --> 00:46:51.420 align:middle line:84%
They're going to
carry on in their day

00:46:51.420 --> 00:46:54.640 align:middle line:84%
with a slight shift
in their being,

00:46:54.640 --> 00:46:56.990 align:middle line:84%
and they're going to
affect the next person.

00:46:56.990 --> 00:46:59.450 align:middle line:84%
In the end, everything's
impermanent.

00:46:59.450 --> 00:47:01.580 align:middle line:90%
Our lives are impermanent.

00:47:01.580 --> 00:47:05.580 align:middle line:84%
And everything around
us is impermanent.

00:47:05.580 --> 00:47:07.800 align:middle line:90%
Our friends, the work we do.

00:47:07.800 --> 00:47:10.440 align:middle line:84%
Anything we can create
will eventually fade away

00:47:10.440 --> 00:47:12.240 align:middle line:90%
and will be forgotten.

00:47:12.240 --> 00:47:15.540 align:middle line:84%
And that can be a
terrifying thought.

00:47:15.540 --> 00:47:18.300 align:middle line:84%
It can have us
reach out for things

00:47:18.300 --> 00:47:20.790 align:middle line:84%
that will give us
some kind of solidity.

00:47:20.790 --> 00:47:23.700 align:middle line:84%
But in the end, that's
all an illusion.

00:47:23.700 --> 00:47:25.980 align:middle line:90%
Security is an illusion.

00:47:25.980 --> 00:47:29.550 align:middle line:84%
And until we can make
peace with the fact

00:47:29.550 --> 00:47:33.970 align:middle line:84%
of ultimately our
own mortality, I

00:47:33.970 --> 00:47:37.000 align:middle line:90%
don't think we're truly living.

00:47:37.000 --> 00:47:38.920 align:middle line:90%
I think we somehow--

00:47:38.920 --> 00:47:42.040 align:middle line:84%
there's a tension inside
of us that we're holding,

00:47:42.040 --> 00:47:45.430 align:middle line:84%
and it doesn't really
allow us to be free.

00:47:45.430 --> 00:47:52.460 align:middle line:90%


00:47:52.460 --> 00:47:54.860 align:middle line:84%
I've done these
artworks as memorials

00:47:54.860 --> 00:47:58.460 align:middle line:84%
where people are coming
together to remember

00:47:58.460 --> 00:48:02.840 align:middle line:90%
someone who has died.

00:48:02.840 --> 00:48:04.850 align:middle line:84%
And we create something
beautiful together.

00:48:04.850 --> 00:48:07.760 align:middle line:84%
And then with the knowledge
that it will wash away,

00:48:07.760 --> 00:48:11.202 align:middle line:84%
which really is kind
of the passage of life.

00:48:11.202 --> 00:48:16.620 align:middle line:90%


